name: Mount Bromo
description:
Mount Bromo or in the Tenggerese spelled "Brama", also called the Tengger Caldera, is an active volcano in East Java, Indonesia. This mountain has a height of 2,329 meters above sea level and is located in four districts, namely Probolinggo Regency, Pasuruan Regency, Lumajang Regency, and Malang Regency. Mount Bromo is famous as the main tourist attraction in East Java. As a tourist attraction, Bromo becomes interesting because of its status as an active volcano. Mount Bromo is included in the Bromo Tengger Semeru National Park area.

*) This work is a part of charity, 100% of primary sales will be donated for the victims of the natural disaster of Mount Semeru eruption.
